In this presentation, I talk about artificial intelligence and machine learning and explain how computers learn from data and use patterns to make predictions and decisions. I also describe the difference between AI and machine learning, the main types of machine learning, and some real-world applications such as recommendation systems, navigation apps, healthcare, and fraud detection. In addition, I briefly discuss the benefits and risks of AI, including efficiency, automation, bias, privacy concerns, and the effect AI may have on jobs and everyday life.
